\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid4202737 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you give your name and address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Mrs Jeannie Williams, 11, Cwmorthin Road, Blaenau F}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13641882\charrsid13268011 f}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 estiniog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Are you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did you get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I was married in 1914.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - I can't remember the year, but I'll be seventy-nine next September. I was born on th
e ninth of September but I don't remember which year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where were you born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 In Talsarnau. (VILLAGE)
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many years did you live in the house in which you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't know, my mother moved to a small farm after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how old you were when you moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No I don't. And then we went to another little farm called Wern on Morfa Harlech and then we went from Wern over the fields to Glasfryn, a bigger farm and it was from there that I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Then did you move up to Blaenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, I went to live in Talsarnau for a little while and my oldest son was born in South Wales and then I left South Wales and moved back to Talsarnau and then I came to Blaenau Ffestiniog and then I went to Oakley Square wher
e I was for twelve years, and then we moved from Oakley Square to Conglog and we were there for eighteen years except for a few days. I've been down here since 1949.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember why you had to make these moves?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well my husband came to work in Blaenau, that's why I had to leave Talsarnau, because he worked in the quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about when you were a child, why did you move around then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - my mother and father moved so we had to do the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was your father moving around with his job or changing his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well you see, he used to work for Lord Harlech and he used to use the little farm that we used to live on as a sort of extra, he could get a - make a little money by working there after he came from doing Lord Harlech's farm. Glyn Talsarnau that is.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many brothers and sisters did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I had William and John, brothers, and my mother lost one as a baby and then there was Mag, Kate, Nell, Mary, Nance and me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 So that's six girls and two boys altogether?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What order did they come in? Who was the oldest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh - one of the girls was the oldest, Margaret. She's dead now. And then William and he's dead too, and Kate next and - she lives in Talabont Duffryn. And then the one that - tha
t my mother lost next, he was very small. And then me, and then my sister that lives in Llan Frothen next and then my sister that lives in Barmouth next, she's got a big camp in Barmouth at Llanaber, and the other son next and then the youngest daughter.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how many years there were between the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well there was about two years between them, that is two years between the brothers and sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how old your father was when you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How old was your father when he died and what year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he was seventy-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What year was that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he's been dead now for thirty-eight or thirty-nine years, and my mother died within two weeks, in fact less than two weeks after
 he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How old was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she was seventy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did your father come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 From Llandecwyn, Talsarnau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well first of all when he was a boy of twelve he went to look after a horse at a place called Cefn
 Gwyn, that's what I heard them say anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 After that did he work on the farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, he did that but he always had a - a small f}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16007366\charrsid13268011 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 rm of his own. But when he went to work for Lord Harlech at Glasgryn there was enough work for him at home as it was then, and - and in fact there was enough work for him and the oldest son.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 So he was at home on the farm then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 'Cos there were eight milking cows and two horses. It would be so nice if I could find the pictures I had of them, the pictures that 
were taken in the yard, the farmyard. The pictures were taken with only the two horses and a cart.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did this farm belong to him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, he paid rent to Lord Harlech.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he do any part time jobs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, he did, he used to be a gravedigger. He did that for a bit. And he was a bell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16007366\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 ringer in the church, the church of Llanfihangoe and that's where we used to go when we were children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you ever remember your father being out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did your mother come from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she came from Rhyd Gosh, Talsarnau, that's on Talsarnau Island in fact.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she have a job before she got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No she didn't, she was at home with her mother and father. There were only two daughters and she'd go and do
 the washing for the church cottage and another house, and she used to help out like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about after she got married, did she work at all, did she do any part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean my mother? No she didn't. No, I don't think she did work after she got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how many rooms there were in your houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I remember Glasfryn. But I don't remember very much about Wern, which is where we were before we went to Glasfryn. There were four - no, five bedrooms and a parlo
ur and a kitchen and a dairy and a pantry where we churned. And then there was a boiler house where we boiled up potatoes for the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16007366\charrsid13268011  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 pigs and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if any people apart from your parents and brothers and sisters lived in the house with y
ou, did you have a lodger or relatives living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother pay anyone to help her in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was the washing all done in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother or father make and mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well yes, my mother would make them. She'd make us plain frocks and aprons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she mend the clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, she did. Oh goodness yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you usually have new clothes or second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16007366\charrsid13268011  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - you've never seen so few new clothes. But we were tidy and the old dear'd be at it, you know, all hours - mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did you buy clothes if you bought new clothes, what place did you go to?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well there was this old lady who used to live at Y
nys and she used to go up to Blaenau with a cart with a - a pony in front of it, and she'd go to Blaenau shop and she'd bring lots of things from there and my mother would buy a coat or a skirt for us. Obviously they were old fashioned, nobody'd be seen d
ead in them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there a special time at which you got new clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No. Except that we did get them in the summer. We'd get a new frock that somebody had made - my mother had made.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't have new clothes before the Gymanfa?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we did if we could. A little something maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother buy second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16007366\charrsid13268011  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 hand clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - you see what usually happened was that they were passed down, you know, she'd make some clothes and then they got passed down from one to the other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about shoes, did you have new shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well in the summer we'd get new canvas shoes, but we had hobnail boots as a rule, even to to to Sunday school, 'cos we had nearly two miles to walk across the fields to go to Sunday school, and we'd
 have tea ta Ynys and then we'd go to the church in the evening and we'd have hobnail boots which had been polished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would these be new or second hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - new.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your father help your mother with jobs around the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, he had plenty of work to do with the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 He didn't clean or cook or wash?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he do any decorating or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, he didn't. But of course Lord - it belonged to Lord Harlech so he was responsible for it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your father dress or undress you or give you a bath ever?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he go out with you without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he look after you when your mother went out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I've no recollection of that, my eldest sister tended to look after me. She kept command.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you as children have jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we had to make sure we'd done this and that before we went to school. And then when we came home we were supposed to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long did you have to go on doing jobs around the house, did you keep on doing that after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, because - when I left school I went to be a servant to the Methodist Minister i
n Talsarnau. I was fourteen and I went straight from school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about your brothers and sisters, did they have tasks to do around the house too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, and my older brother, - well he was on the farm with my father.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if th
e older children helped the younger children with things that they found difficult, like how to eat and how to put their clothes on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't remember. Not like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember the younger children having to do things for the older ones at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 The younger ones were treated - they got much more fair play than we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents expect you to go to bed at a particular time while you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we could never be late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who put you do bed?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well you know - my mother was at home all the time sort of holding - the fort, so she would unless she asked my older sister to do it.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how old you were when you went to bed on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you share your bedroom with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - only with my sisters.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
You said there were five bedrooms in the house, did your mother and father have one on their own and then the children were spread out in the other ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, that's right. I think it was two in each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about having baths, did you have a tub in front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, those old fashioned things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did you have to have a bath as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - every week. Not - not every day like they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was that on Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about having clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had clean clothes regularly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 In the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. If we - spoke or made a noise and my father'd be sitting in the corner frow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13641882\charrsid13268011 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
ing, look out. My father was very strict really. Not like it is now. Children have become the masters now haven't they. And if we were bad we might be sent to eat in the scullery or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember eating in the parlour or anything on a special occasion? When you had visitors for instance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well you see, the thing was my younger brother became a cripple after he was in the army and - fits had taken him over and so my mother had to put
 a bed in the parlour for him. 'Cos he had fits you see. He'd been ruined - he'd been in a damp place in the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was this the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, it was. And he died. My father tried everything, only he got nothing. It had affected his spine
. They pulled all his teeth out and everything. Everything we could think of to try and make him better. We took him to Llandrindod Wells, to the hospital there and everything, and we had to carry him everywhere so we had to leave a bed downstairs in the 
parlour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about cooking, what did your mother cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she had an old fashioned oven and she baked everything herself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did you have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well when we were going to school we had breakfast fairly early. Because we had 
about a mile to walk to get to school and obviously we walked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were all the members of the family present at breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well yes they were as far as I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you usually have to eat or drink for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I'm sure it was tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if you liked it, bacon or a boiled egg or porridge.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there any day when you got a different breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. There wasn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about dinner and supper, when did you have those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we'd have potatoes and we killed pigs ourselves so we'd have bacon or ham and I think it was only on Sundays that we had fresh meat.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have dinner at midday?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - for supper we'd have a cup of tea and a big bowl of bread and milk, and bread and butter if we wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was this about seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. About then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have tea at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we used to have tea and bread and butter say, if we wanted it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You said your mother baked bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I've no memory of her making pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about wine or medicine for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 She didn't make beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother and father grow their fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
You mean like carrots? Yes they did, potatoes, carrots, cabbage, Swedes and lettuce, and we had to take these in the holidays or on every Friday night into Harlech in a sort of box which had been made into a sort of pram and we'd sell them. Yes we did.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they buy vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - don't talk of that. No. It was hard enough to get rid of what we'd got, sometimes we had to go twice i
n a week to sell them to people. And we sold peas and French beans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember any dried or tinned vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Which animals did they have on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they had eight milking cows and I should say about eight calves and bullocks, and I'm not sure if they didn't have a few sheep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about hens and pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, they had those. And ducks and geese.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - anyone that take - would take them food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did you have meat to eat in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - you see we'd get stew sometimes and we'd have meat in that. But you see if my father went to Port on business he'd bring back a lump of beef, but apart from that it was only on Sundays that we had fresh meat. But we killed our own pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember your parents getting extra meat from poaching at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, my father didn't like something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember your mother having less food in order that the family should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your father get more food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he'd get as much as he could eat really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you talk at mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, we couldn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you allowed to choose what you wanted to eat or did you eat what was given?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had to take what was given.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if you left food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well we had pigs you see, it went to those.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Your parents didn't mind it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13641882\charrsid13268011 Well we very }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
rarely left food on the plate so it didn't really happen very often. I get so angry now you know, my grandchildren when they leave food uneaten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If there was something on the table that you wanted, like the salt, were you allowed to ask for it or wait 'til it was offered to you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if it was on the table as a rule we'd reach across for it, unless somebody else was using it of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they expect you to hold the knife and fork in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I can't remember honestly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they emphasise that you should sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - we couldn't misbehave at the table, that's for sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you allowed to bring books or toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, we weren't. No, we couldn't eat - we couldn't read while eating. - That was for after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you leave the table when you wanted to or wait 'til everyone else had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, you waited 'til everyone had finished and then everyone'd get up together and go off to their work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did all the family sit at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who served the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well yes, my mother really. My best memories of this are, you know, while I was at school because I left - left home as soon as I left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember in what order the food was served out, did your father get served first and then the children in order of age?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When your mother served the food out did she give it to your father first and then to the children in any particular order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the thing was that the food was on the table and we all came together to the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did your younger brothers and sisters sit before they were old enough to sit at the table? Did they have a high chair or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, well you see they came from outside straight the table and there'd be a bowl by the - by the door, a bowl for washing your hands, a bench with a bowl on it and water in it and they could wash their hands if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about when your brothers and sisters were babies, where did they sit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I'm afraid I can't remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't have a maid did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was your mother an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she show affection to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you share your worries with her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you talk to your father easily?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well no. No not so much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he show you affection?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - he'd be -working 'til it was time to go to bed, he didn't 
really have time. And, you know, when he was resting between work and going to bed, well if we made a noise he'd give us a row.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did your parents expect you to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I don't think any one of us ever misbehaved towards th
em. I've no recollection of that. But - except for my younger brother, but then he couldn't help it, because he had fits and you had to watch him all the time you see, he'd gone like that. But I mean he didn't do it purposefully.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents brin
g you up to think that certain things were important in life? And to behave towards your brothers and sisters in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. They did. I remember - one of my sisters - singing while she was churning and my father wasn't in a very good temp
er and he shouted out that she could only do one job at a time and she replied that she could do both just as well, and he was very disapproving of this. I mean there was no harm in singing while you're churning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did they expect you to behave towards your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - we weren't to make a noise so we weren't to quarrel in front of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If a child hit you were you allowed to hit him back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well they never had a chance to disapprove or approve 'cos we didn't do it in front of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of person would you say your parents wanted you to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, they wanted us to be obedient to everyone and kindly towards everyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they bring you up to think that some things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if we did do certain things we'd get a mouthful from them, if we did something that is.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they feel that the chapel or the church were important in life for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we used to have to go. Oh yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did they feel about swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You can guess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When adults were talking were you allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 We'd be sent out for a run.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If you did something that your parents disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I don't really remember having ever done anything that they disapproved of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember being punished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Would you say that you received the ideas about how to behave from your mother and father or did one of them play a more important part than the other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't think one was more important, I think both of them were fairly similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Both of them affected you in the same way would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I'm sure they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about birthdays, were they special?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. We didn't have birthdays in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't have presents or anything special to eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we'd get a little bit of something, but very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have anything special to eat or do anything special on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we'd have a Christmas dinner - with a goose or something.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, there wasn't anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about singing, did anyone in your family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, my father used to conduct choirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the family ever make music together, have a musical evening in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, very little. But sometimes when my father was practicing the whole choir would come to our house to practice. Or else he'd go to - 
they'd all go down to the school, which was more usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents play games with you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, my father would play draughts.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were there books in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, but I don't think they were very important books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about newspapers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I think they used to get the Herald or something. A welsh newspaper, they didn't get an English one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they didn't have any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember seeing your mother and father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Only the paper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they read aloud to you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember a funeral in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I remember my brother's funeral, my younger brother. I was living in Blaenau at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember a funeral when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if a lot of people went to your brother's funeral in Blaenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, they did. A lot of people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember them wearing special mourning clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well everybody wore black clothes in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if the ceremony was different from what it is today?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I don't know, we brought my brother's body from - from up the mountain, -the - above Harlech, there were miles to bring him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was he brought down with a horse cart?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, no, it - with a hearse, like they have today you know, a motor hearse, and there were cars too. And I didn't do the whole distance, I met them on the way because I had rheumatism in my feet in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember going to visit friends, neighbours and relatives as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't go out and visit people at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about going out shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I'd go once a week, and I'd take butter to the shop in Talsarnau. I'd go with a bike.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you'd usually go shopping on your own would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember going shopping with your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Or your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well - sometimes there'd be a special outing somewhere, but it was only rarely. You know, when they wanted to buy something special.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember going out with you father alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Not even for a grip somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Only to the church. Jesus Christ.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember going on a trip with your mother anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember having a holiday at all as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you spend Saturdays in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we'd be at it all day you know, we'd be at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Working on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes
. And we used to have to carry water in those days, we used to have a sort of cask on wheels, we have to - we used to have to carry two of those full every Saturday to be ready for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you spend Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we couldn't do anything on Sunday, except for just the milking and feeding the calves, and feeding the pigs and feeding the hens.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you wear different clothes on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes we did, Sunday - Sunday clothes, but we'd have to take them off as soon as we got home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you allowed to play games at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother and father feel it was wrong to work or play on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh my father went to church but my mother didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Your mother didn't go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did your father go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well every Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times in that day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he went every morning and every evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have to go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we used to have to go across the f
ields and he'd go along the Post Road with a bike. We had to walk across the fields. But it was a bit further to go with the bike, 'cos obviously it was quicker. You see, he rang the bell in the church as he was a bell}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13641882\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 ringer and he was a gravedigger too for the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes we did. Yes, we certainly did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember Sunday school trips?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Yes we did. I mean the gymanfa. It wasn't a Sunday school trip, we just had the gymanfa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember any other social activities connected with the church at all, things like the gymanfa, were there other things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No there weren't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 There was no Band of Hope or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we used to go to Glanwern where the school was to make Bank of Ho
pe. And we had a mile to go to that, and I wouldn't go now. No, I'd be too frightened to go now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember why your mother didn't go to church?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I'm not very sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was it because she didn't believe in God?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no. No, it wasn't that. No. She didn't go out very much, my mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the choir, did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well yes, I was - I was a member of my father's choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of things did you do with the choir?
