Well there was a sort of - competitive meeting, singing and things, in Talsarnau, and eistedfords and things you mean. Yes, and we used to win there, singing and reciting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember going to the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't - I didn't know what they were. I'd no idea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents give you pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no. Didn't think about pocket money in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did anyone come when there was trouble in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No.
 Well - maybe somebody came on - when we were milling - milling the flour, and maybe' someone'd come in and help my mother at lunchtime on that day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any relatives around who came in to look after the children or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, there were relatives but they weren't around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well she was ill you know, I went home and looked after her after I got married. She was ill for a pretty long spell.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did she manage when she had your younger sisters and brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I can't say who was with her then, but I remember that my eldest sister was with her when she had the youngest. I only remember her being born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You said there weren't any neighbours living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. They lived pretty far really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever go and visit with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I'm sure we went at the time of the gymanfa in Barmouth, 'cos there was a brother of my mother's there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents have friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well as far as I know they were friends with everyone. They weren't out quarrellin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13641882\charrsid13268011 g}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011  with anyone.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did they go and visit with their friends? Did they go to their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the friends come to your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh sometimes. But otherwise, you know, they met in the - the village or the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say your parents shared similar friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well as far as I know, yes, and they were friends with everyone, everyone around the place. I don't think they had any enemies at all.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mother have any special friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I do}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2836659\charrsid13268011 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
't think so. Yes, my mother did have, she lived in Bryn Golau in Blaenau Ffestiniog. She was a special friend.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And did she come up to Blaenau to see her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Very rarely. You've never seen so - so little visiting. I mean she hardly came up to see me when I was living in Blaenau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your father have any special friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If friends came round to your house were they offered something to eat or drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, yes, if somebody came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did they come?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they didn't come very often. No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there any special day that they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that the friends that came to visit were your father's friends or your mother's friends or friends of both?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean the lady I said about in Blaenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Anyone who came and had tea or something with you? Were they your mother's and father's friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, they were. But you know - very few came really. Nobody came in those days, it was not the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did people come without invitations?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, of course, if they came.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents go visiting friends and neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 People tell us that in those days people had to make their own amusements, there weren't televisions or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, there was nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember your parents making their own amusements with friends or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - all my mother'd do would be mend socks and things in the evening, you know, after s
he'd finished everything else and my father, well, we used to see him having a smoke and lying on the sofa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
People divide society up into different classes or groups, would you say that before 1918 some people belonged to one class or group and other people belonged to another one? Do you remember if this was the way you saw things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I was in Blaenau in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Don't you remember feeling that Lord Harlech and people were big people and different to ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. Becau
se I'll tell you - I'd gone into this little - well, copse really, of trees and I cut this green tree within about - oh a few inches of the ground, no, it wasn't green it was dry, and a steward came along on a - on his horse, and he came into the yard to 
m
y father. Good morning, Mr Hughes, he said, who's been cutting that tree over there? I don't know, my father said. If my daughter's been I don't know. Well you'd better look after your place better than that, he said. And it was me that had done it. Well 
it was dry. It was dead. And that's the only time I remember them coming, there was nothing else that they came for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people would you say belonged to the same group or class as you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well all the people around where we lived they were - they were very similar.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - you know - all sorts of different people, working - and farms and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How would you describe people who belonged to a different class, people who felt maybe that they were superior to the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well round us there - there weren't any you know, there was only ordinary people. Except for - for those you know. There was only Lord Harlech and - and everybody else was much the same. Similar to us you know, to - to wha
t we were like, our way of living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember being brought up to respect some people in a different way to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - we had to respect everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember curtseying, touching your cap or any of those things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people did you do that to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I'll tell you, Lord Harlech used to make tea for the schoolchildren, the schoolchildren of Glanwkrn - every year, a sort of a annual tea party, and Glanwern was
 Lord Harlech's school in fact, and boys couldn't be there after they were twelve, it was all girls then, and we'd have tea and a big sort of splash in Glyn - Glyn Hall and of course we had to bow and everything to them, and to the people from Caerffynnon
 in Talsaranau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you ever remember calling anyone sir or master or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't. Unless it was Sir Evan Jones from - the quarry. - Rhyosydd.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in the form of a curtsey or sir or master or madam or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who would you say were the important people in your area?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't know. Maybe Jones Morris from Ynys. He was the father of Doc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011 t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 or Morris in portmadoc you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Why would you say he was important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I don't know, he was - you know he used to play the organ in the church and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you come into contact with people like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did the shopkeepers mix with would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 The shopkeepers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 The shopkeepers from Talsarnau for instance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they stick together or mix with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I mean they mixed with everyone to the extent that they wanted to sell things of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the Ministers, did they mix al right with everyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes. But they - he was a bit - well I think he's alive now. Oh I'd like to see him. I'd like to see him. He must be over ninety. That's where I went as a servant you know, that's the only place I went to and my other sister went there
 after me and then my sister, the one that's in Barmouth now, she went there after that, and I went back afterwards. And they buried their son since - what - about a year and a half or two years ago now. He was a schoolmaster in Ruthin in the County schoo
l, Ruthin. And that's how I heard about you know what he was doing now. And he was over ninety. Oh I'd like to see him, if he's alive that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did the farmers and teachers mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - the farmers, well they - they did mix but they tended to stick together I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh there was only one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he mix in with everyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she was a lady,. Miss Mynet. And she was quite sociable.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about employers, did they mix with ordinary people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No they didn't. They kept to themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people would you say went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well all sorts of people like now, but not many people go now, to the church or the chapel. Oh they were very - you know - easy going people, everyone got along all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about chapel people, did you feel that chapel people and church people were different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they - you know, they - they got on, they co-operated with each other. But now they don't you know, everybody wants to be on their own
 somehow and there's no Christianity in something like that. There isn't you know. They're jealous of each other now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that in your area the workers had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, much the same I'd say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You wouldn't say that there were different groups within the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well they didn't have much time to mix together really. You know, when they - only when they went to sales or something you know, that they could get - meet each other as a group, because you kn
ow, the farmers were very sort of separate. But if you know, they wanted to borrow something or - needed some help to do something oh they - they'd certainly have that sort of help from other farmers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember some people being very poor and others with money within the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well you know it was very poor, and we were very poor after we came to Blaenau, with the wages. But you see it was different farmers 'cos they had something to fall back on. I mean, you know, the sub in Blaenau 
was one pound sixteen and eleven when we came here. I know, I've been through lots of things you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember feeling that some workers felt themselves superior to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, there were a lot of those too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember some families being described as rough and others as respectable?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't. No, I've no recollection of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember any distinction being made between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you think your mother and father had the same attitude to people of different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I - I'm sure - I'm sure they were the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you think your mother saw herself belonging to a particular class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if it was possible in t
hose days to move from one class to another, if you were poor could you work your way up and become something important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, it's possible - it's possible you know with lots of things to do that, to improve yourself that is, but you must take an in
terest in doing so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember anyone doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What you mean when I was young? No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember later on, have you ever heard anyone described in that way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I haven't. People were much more alike in - you know in the days that have gone by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember seeing a policeman around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh don't talk about it, I am so frightened I nearly died. I am so frightened when I see a policeman. Dear mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the policeman treat people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I don't remember him coming to our house while I was at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember hearing about how he treated other people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't. They were - they weren't po
licemen in the old days you know. Not so terrible anyway. Not as terrible as they are today. Oh no, they weren't, they're nothing like what they are today. I'm so frightened of them you know. Oh dear mother. I'm still frightened you know. And they pick on
 some people you know and - you know - book you for everything, and they leave a lot of others. We can see you know. They shut their}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011  eyes to so man}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 . What I say is that they should do the same to everyone. Everyone should be treated equally. And they shouldn
't go round houses asking people if they've seen this or seen that. They get paid don't they, they should work for that money and not drag other people into their affairs. I'm terribly frightened of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes, it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember seeing anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, I - you see I used to feel they were a step above. They'd never come to our place you know unless we were behind with the rent 
or something like that. No, they wouldn't come near the place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember feeling that your parents had trouble making ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't think so, we had plenty of food all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did it make any different to you if your father was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - I'll tell you, he was only ill in his bed for about three weeks in his whole life as far as I remember and I was called there on a Saturday and he was dead on Monday. He was ill for three weeks before he died, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember having charity from the parish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh goodness no. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
If there was a person in your area that people disapproved of very much was there any special way of showing this disapproval, a way of showing that the community didn't want these people around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't remember.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember them making rough music outside houses for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember straw men or effigies being made? And marched through the streets at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Before you went to school did you have any lessons at home from your parents or a private tutor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if we had homework we had to do it at home. We had to do it the night before.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 But you didn't have any sort of lessons before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, no, we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How old were you when you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How - oh I don't know. We lived far away you know, it was a long way to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you about six?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I'm sure I was. Yes, I must have been about five to six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you first started school what time in the morning did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we had to be in school by nine and we'd come back at half past three. And we walked remember, there was nothing to take us, nothing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You always went to afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes we did and we took our own food with us. We'd take bread and milk in a tin or maybe sandwiches on one day. Then we put them inside the fireguard in the school, that's how we had to be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of school was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well it wasn't a very big school. There was only one building and there was a gallery up there and classes like this and then the school house - was fixed on and
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And girls and boys went there did they?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Until the boys were n
ine. It was nine I think, not twelve as I said before. Nine. Yes it was nine. And then the boys had to go to Talsarnau. Because they were too much to manage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the school belong to Lord Harlech?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes, it did. She was English you know - the schoolmistress that is. There was only her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have to speak a lot of English in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we did. Everything was in English. I'm surprised that I can't speak English properly actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you walked to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long did it take to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I'm sure it was about a mile and a half. Yes, a good mile and a half and we had to go there and come back. It must have taken three quarters of an hour - hour maybe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who went with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the sister nearest to me and I don't know if my brother didn't go too, if I remember correctly, and the other sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You took your dinner with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you like school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I did, I didn't want to miss any days. No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards the teacher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I was very good friends with her. Yes I was. Only I did get two slaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What had you done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we were washing the dusters after she'd unlocked the door in the morning and it - there was a very, you k
now, empty noise - the noise of us running in the empty school. You see, the - the maid opened the door and then - and we rushed in, everybody was racing to get the dusters in order to dust, and she came there, I heard some noise, she said. And she put us
 
all in a line and told us to hold out our hands and gave us a hell of a slap. I didn't cry though. And then the next day I went - climbed up this - sort of cliff at lunchtime and we were a little bit late getting back to the school and she asked us where 
we'd been and we told her. And we got another one. But I mean I wasn't sort of - upset by this because I knew it was my fault. And the others too you know. No the poor creature, she was O.K.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the schoolmistress emphasise that some things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we used to have scripture and a man, an inspector would come there. She used to emphasise that a lot, scripture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she emphasise manners and tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And being on time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, and - and with sewing too and things like that. If we did anything wrong in the sewing we had to undo it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember her emphasizing ways of speaking, did you have to speak pure language or correct language?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no she didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You've talked about being punished, what did she use, the birch rod?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh the cane, the cane. I can visualize it now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the boys and girls get the same punishments?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Yes they did. And whoever had committed a crime, however many of us there were we all got the same punishment.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of things did you get punished for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents show an interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well yes, they did with sewing and marking and things. But I mean we didn't have reports or anything like they do now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they ask you what you'd done at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the thing was that we got the things, we were given them, the things we'd made. We'd have a tea}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 party and then we'd get things. Everybody'd have their present and if you hadn't missed any school then you get a better present.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents go and see the teachers or see the school at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that the other children at the school came from the same sorts of homes as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - they were all pretty similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember the teacher singling out some children for different treatment to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - the odd one would get a slap, especially if they were eating sweets in the class room or something, 
'cos they weren't supposed to do that. They'd gat a slap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember her making favourites of anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember gangs or groups of children at school doing things together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember some children being left out of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go to another school after this one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you have stayed on if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well you
 see this Minister was after my mother and father and after me you know all the time, trying to get me to leave before I was fourteen in order to go to them and work for them, but I couldn't - he tried every way to try and get me to leave. Even tried the 
County. But I wasn't allowed to leave school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever have any part time education like night school or anything after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you regret anything about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't. I managed all right on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you think you benefited from going to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I'm sure I did didn't I. But you know I've no idea what this new money is you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 While you were at school did you have a part time job to gather a bit of regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You only had one full time job didn't you, the one with the Minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes, that's right. I used to have to look after the children and - and look after the house and the children when they went away. And clean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you get that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - he'd be going to the chapel on a Sunday and I'd be going to Sunday school - church Sunday school, and he said he liked me and they'd like to have me there for the older boy. He was very small then of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many hours did you work for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I worked all - all - through the day, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your work Saturdays and Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes, but they used to let me go to church - morning and afternoon one Sunday and afternoon and evening the next one. And she we
nt - alternately.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever have holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they pay you? How much did you get?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I used to get seven pounds for six months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you think this was fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh Lord, I mean, I'd get - I'd get that in a week n
ow, and I used to have a night out, w'd set out at five o'clock from the Minister's house, I'd walk two miles home to my mother and father's house. I only used to go home - and he'd want me to be back by nine, and she'd say to him, William now don't be ha
rd, remember that Jeannie's going home. So - then I'd have to be back by ten. Two miles I had to go.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you give the money you earned to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did, but if I'd had clothes then I'd have to pay for those before - you know, before anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did your mother spend the money on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
On food and things, yes. Or else, you know, she'd pay for something that - I'd had - when I started you know, something that hadn't been paid for yet. It was very different in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you get along with the people you worked for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. Very well. Except for one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I went to the seaside in Talsarnau and I took the Minister's little boy with me and two sisters and Mrs Bob Griffiths from Twrna in Bla
enau, she was a cousin, and we'd gone over the river and didn't think about the tide coming in and when we came back to the river the big river the tide was coming in and we - and we couldn't - you know, we couldn't cross. And I had to lift my skirts up l
i
ke this and - and - and carry them on my back, and their feet were in the water and a - and a boy came who the village of Talsarnau and he was up on the cliff top and he was us and I called out to him and - otherwise we'd have drowned. The others - you kn
ow, if I hadn't been able to go back for the others they'd have drowned too. I got a mouthful then from them, from him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards the Minister as an employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I was all right with him, and her too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards the work you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - you know, I did it - as it came.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did starting work change your attitude to school, did you regret that you'd left school after you started working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no I didn't. No, I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many servants did the minister have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did you eat? And sleep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we ate in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you eat with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I used to look after the children while they were eating. And then I would have my fo
od on my own afterwards. But I had my own bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have anywhere where you could go when you weren't working, apart from your bedroom where you could be alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I was just in the kitchen and dining room, he'd be up in the study of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about eating in the dining room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh no they ate in the kitchen unless there were visitors and then they ate in the dining room. And then I'd have to put a white apron on and a black - black frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the mistress supervise you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she was a very nice woman. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel O.K. towards her and happy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, yes, I did, very happy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you call the members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I called him Mr Griffiths and Mrs Griffiths to her and the childr
en by their names. Oh it's just the same as if I was at home you know. I was part of the family.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they take an interest in you as a person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your mistress give you any moral guidance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - the thing was I don't 
think I ever did anything out of place. I only - you know, saw my work and I knew my work so - and I stuck to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any free time to do what you liked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, in the evening after the children had gone to bed. I could sew or something then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about leaving the house, going home and things like that, going out in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I've told you, it was just the one night I went home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel homesick?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I did. But only for the first two nights, I cried bitterly then, I cried myself to sleep.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Didn't you have any friends there or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I didn't have any friends. Everyone was strange.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there anything you liked or disliked particularly about your situation in the Minister's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't think so, I was very happy there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the housework go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh it - it was champion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the mistress do some of the work too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well she looked after the food, but I used to have to peel the potatoes. But ten she did the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I did the washing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about mending and making the family}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 s clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well I used to mend some and she mended some.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did the improvements or repairs to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 O the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You looked after the children, how many children were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well there was Blevin, Roy, Vera, Willie Lloyd, Peggie and Griffie. Six children. But Peggie and Gracie were - were twins, and Gracie died when she was young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you have to do with the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh well - they had a - they had a bath in the evening before they went to bed and then when they got up in the morning I'd have to give them a wash and dress them, and their food would be ready. And then they'd go off to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How much did the children see of their parents, did they see a lot of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No - not much. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were they with you most of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I'd take them out you see. If they didn't go to school I'd take them out somewhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take them for walks or go shopping or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I'd take them for walks. Sometimes there'd be two in the pram or maybe one would be walking and just one in the pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children see the parents anywhere in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children have any jobs to do around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. They were very small. They were only small when - when the Minister moved from Talsarnau and then we went to Denyolen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you move with the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 But as they grew up did they have things to do in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well I wasn't there when they grew up because my sisters were there then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You'd got married by then had you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes, I had. I was there when they were born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember if the children helped each other with things they found difficult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did the children go to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you put them to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember how old the children were when they started to go to bed on their own, or had you left?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I'd left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children share a bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - well there were two sleeping together. And then the girls slept in a room on her own. 'Cos there was only th
ree when I was first there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many bedrooms were there in the house? Do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No. Wait a minute - four I think. And a study. That was in Talsarnau. But you know, I came through the floor of the bedroom in Denyolen. Yes I did. I'd gone 
up to collect wood right up in the attic, 'cos there was a lot of nice wood up there, and I went in - and my leg came right through the floor, right above the door of the study. But the ma}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011 i}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 d that was with the previous Minister, she came right through up to her waist you know. She could have hurt herself very badly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there a bathroom in the Ministers house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did the children have a bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well if they were very dirty, if they'd been playing in the garden, they had to have one every night.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - again every night if - you know - if they were dirty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh in the kitchen, unless there was a visitor with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children at separately at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, they ate in - in the kitchen but they ate after the - the parents had eaten. They ate with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember any times when the children ate with their parents, at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of cooking equipment did you have in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had a big stove - big old fashioned stove. There weren't any electric stoves or anything like that then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did they have breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - somewhere between eight and nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was everyone there for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I didn't eat with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 But was everyone else there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you eat after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I ate with the children, afterwards. In order that they had peace with their breakfast - I'd be in the study with the
 children. And then the children and I would have breakfast - afterwards. You see, as they had - peace to have breakfast then I'd have p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5452818\charrsid13268011 eace as well, because she'd be i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 n the kitchen while I was having my breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember a time when everybody ever ate together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you usually have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh porridge. That's what it was at those days. There weren't any cereals or anything then. Or a bacon and egg, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh, they had dinner every day - at midday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, supper too. But the children would only have a cup of milk or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have tea? A tea meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - oh yes, you know, bread and butter or something - and jam.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What time did you have supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well they - you see they went to bed at about six o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 That was the children though, when did you have supper, and the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 But you see, the - the minister had a - had a chapel apart from the one in Talsarnau and he had to go - maybe had}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
