\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they ever buy dried or tinned vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they didn't. Nothing in tins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have a garden at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Just a very small one. The smallest you've seen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did the garden?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well he tried to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have any animals at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times in a week did you eat meat there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I'm sure they had meat every day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have tinned meat at all, tinned salmon or corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did. They had tinned salmon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have the same food as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, yes, everything was the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And the children the same as the adults?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were the children allowed to talk during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't know what they did after I left though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 It was you that was strict with them was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they choose what they wanted to eat? Or did they have to accept it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they couldn't choose, they had to take everything. And that time's changed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were they allowed to leave food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. They had to clean their plates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they ask for the salt if it was on the table and they wanted it, or did they have to wait until it was offered to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they couldn't - they had to wait until it was given to them because they might have put too much on if they'd done it themselves.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, if - if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have to hold the knife and fork in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember telling them to hold it correctly or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ask them to sit in a particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they bring books or toys to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they leave the table when they wanted to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - they were taught to ask, please could they leave the table, when they'd finished. I don't know how - how long they - they went on doing that. And the ones, the grandchildren that come here, I mean they've been taught to
 do it too but they very often get up without saying anything and I have to say, hey, and send them back to their seats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did everyone always sit in the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And Mrs Griffiths served the food out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
If the children ever ate with the parents did - were there great preparations made for this, did they have to put clean clothes on or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. They just had a bib in front of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you look after the children always when they ate separately from the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you always eat with the children or sometimes wait 'til they'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I always ate with the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you served the food out for the children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Yes. But ma
ybe when there was porridge their mother would have served it out for them. She'd have prepared it and everything and maybe put it on the table.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the mother or father come in and see the children while they were eating?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he'd gone to his study of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the mother take in interest in what the children had eaten, did she come in and see them, to see if they'd eaten properly and things?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who taught the children table manners, you or their mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh their mother I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was Mrs Griffiths an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, she was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she show affection to you and the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, she did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the Minister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, he was very straightforward you know, he w
as straightforward, but I mean there was nothing between him and me, except for the time when I went to the - to the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she show affection to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes. In his way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the parents expect the children to behave towards them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well, I mean - I'm sure that he would have done something - pretty terrible to them if they'd done something which crossed him. But I never saw them punished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How were they expected to behave towards their brothers and sisters, could they quarrel for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How were they supposed to behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they didn't try to do anything against me.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I thought the world of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12414293\charrsid13268011 Did}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011  you ever tell the children how to behave towards their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I'm sure I - you know - gave them a few instructions.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If the Minister's children were hit by another child were they allowed to hit that child back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, I
 only remember one being like that. But this wasn't in Talsarnau, it was in Denyolen. I only remember one of them not wanting to go to school and really not wanting to go to school because of some - fight in the school, and he was crying and saying he did
n't want to go to school. But I don't really know what it - you know, what had happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 But in principle were the children allowed to hit back if they were hit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, the parents didn't like them to quarrel at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people would you say the Minister wanted his children to grow up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh I don't know you know. Like him I'm sure. I'll tell you who Mrs Griffiths was. She came from the Gorddinon family. That was her family you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the Minister think that certain things were important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't know you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You don't remember him holding forth about anything? Talking seriously about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Well - except that I do remember him reading a sort of a - family sermon and I - in the eveni
ng and you see the thing was the Mrs Griffiths and I'd been in the kitchen and we'd been having fun in the kitchen and I couldn't stop myself laughing. And he stopped the sermon, and he said, I'm prepared to wait for you Jeannie, until you're ready - read
y to listen. I was frightened out of my life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you teach the children that certain things were important in life? So you remember teaching them to respect people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't. You mean the Minister's children? Oh no. I only tried to do that to my own.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that you had the same attitude to the children as the Minister and his wife?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I'm sure I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did the Minister think of swearing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 We were always frightened of doing it in his hearing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you think of swearing? Say if the children swore?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, I never heard them. Nothing like that. I think they were probably a bit young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If adults were talking did the children join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if the children did something that the parents disapproved of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, I don't ever remember them being punished but then I don't remember them doing anything that would get them a - a slap.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How would you say that the parents wanted to bring up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I think they wanted to grow up to respect everybody and be - kind - kind to people. That's the impression I got anyway - definitely.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If there was any trouble in the family do you ever remember siding with the children against the parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember a birthday in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no. There was nothing at all on birthdays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about Christmas Day, do you remember about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, they used to go away at Christmas, they'd go home to her - her family. They
'd always do that at Christmas. And I wasn't there at Christmas myself, I went home at Christmas.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember there being musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well there was a piano there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did anyone play?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well she did, 'cos she used to play in the chapel sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there anyone in the family who sang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't think so. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember there being music made in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the parents play games with the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. But in a way they weren't really big enough to play games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you didn't play with them either?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember there being books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Children's books?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Or adults books.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well of course he had a big stock in his study, I was frightened of moving any one from its place there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about newspapers did they have any?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember which ones they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember them having magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't remember them having them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember seeing the mother or father reading?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he'd read out these sermons you know, family sermons, and then we'd have a prayer afterwards.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they read aloud to the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well the children would have gone to bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 They didn't read stories out of books to the children though did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you read to the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember there being a funeral in the Minister's family while you were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take the children out for walks and shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did. Well, no, I didn't go - take them shopping. I used to take the children out for a walk and then I'd take them back to the - to
 the house and then I'd go out shopping myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you talk to people when you were out with the Minister's children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever take the children to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did a few times, just for a walk and then back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the children get on in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh fine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 They liked it did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did your relations and parents call the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 By their names, yes, yes, by their names.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Their Christian names?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 They didn't say master or mistress or mister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did these children call your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever go with your master and mistress away for a Bank Holiday or weekend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I didn't. I only went to Mrs Griffiths' home and that was only for a day in a car.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was she different in her own home to what she was when she was with her husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 She was just the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 It didn't make any difference at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no. They were very nice people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your master and mistress feel it was wrong to play or work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And they went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. And he'd have to go away on Saturday nights to a meeting - chapel meeting - so we were on our own on Saturday - Saturday night.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did it make any difference if he was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. We were must a bit more nervous that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean you were more nervous because he was away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, that's right, 'co
s he'd gone away. You see, he - he might go away - he'd go away on Saturday afternoon and wouldn't come back 'til - Monday, because he'd go away, you know, to his other parish and we'd be by ourselves you see, the mistress and me and the children.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times did they go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he went all the time of course, but she took it in turns with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go to the came chapel as them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well he was a Methodist you see, and she was a Methodist, and I went to church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You said they had family prayers and said grace and things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the Minister take any interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't remember him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Or the mistres}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the Minister take part in sports, play cards, go to races, bet at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't. No, he didn't believe in playing cards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember the mistress going out on her own at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - you know, she was very nervous you see so she couldn't go anywhere on her own. She was very nervous. Her nerves were very bad.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did she do any work for charity at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, she certainly did. If somebody was ill she'd make food for them and I'd have to take it round, in the midd
le of my work, or I'd have to go to Port to get some stuff if I - if it couldn't be got in Talsarnau, and I'd have to go and look for it on the bike all the way to Port - Portmadoc that is - if I couldn't get it in Talsarnau.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember the master and mistress going out together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. They'd got the Seate at Ynys. And she'd go with him and I'd be at home by myself then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the mistress ever go away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. She was at home of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have a lot of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did - they ever come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes they did. 'Cos that's when I had to put on my black dress and white apron.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And - they had food and things to drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was it a very big occasion when they came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of people would you say came to see the Ministers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh I can't remember his job, but he was the one that used to come most often. Mr Roberts from Cefn Trefor, but he's been dead for years of course. He - he used to come, and he went to the Methodist chapel of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that the people who came were from the same class as your master and mistress? Were they the same type of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What class would you say your employer came from, or from which group in society would you say he was from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he was a pretty high man you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And the mistress too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the master and mistress treat some of their friends differently to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 They respected everyone the same did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did their friends behave towards you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh all right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did some treat you differently from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No, they used to tease me enough though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that your master and mistress were satisfied with their lives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes they were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 They didn't want to climb higher or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Had you known people like your master and mistress before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. I mean I knew him before you see, but I - I wasn't acquainted with her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you feel about the way they lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I thought they lived very nicely. Yes I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they behave differently from people you had known before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were they fairly ordinary then in their behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Have you done any other job apart from the one you did for the Minister, after the first world war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean after I left the Minister? No, I didn't go anywhere after that, I got married you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If you could live your life again would you have done another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I wouldn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You never served an apprenticeship or training period did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that workers and employers had the same inter
est, that they see the world in the same way? Or would you say there was a conflict of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well do you mean like this, that some people get more fair play than others? Is that what you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say for instance that workers tend to try and get as much money as they can from their work and then the employer .....?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh and - and then - and then - the employer tries to give them as little, that's what you mean isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 So you think the world is like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, and there
's a great unfairness there. The worker always gets the least. The owners always get the advantage all the time, they have the advantage and the worker doesn't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember a great distinction between craftsmen and workers, do you remembe
r people respecting craftsmen more, or treating them differently to the ordinary labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean more than for a labourer? Oh yes, I'm sure they did. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well what I feel is that both were workers in 
a way, except that one had just had a little bit more education than the other. But you know a lot of people cl}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
mb up from nothing now. I mean take Derek for instance, I mean he's had you know hardly any schooling and he's - he's a - he's a very good joine
r. He - he used to make coffins with this man in - in Penrhyn while he was at school, and after he left school. And now he can do lots of things, you know, for himself or alterations and things. He's made beautiful big windows. And you have to have the in
c
lination to do all this. You need a strong mind to try - to try and do something like that. To learn that sort of craft. But I mean, about the children, I mean they don't try and do anything. All their interested in is kicking a ball. Or else they go to t
he Welsh League of youth and play - beddington or badminton or something. But I don't know, that won't do them any good will it. I quarrel like mad with them you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that working changed your attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well you're supposed to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did working full time affect the way you saw the world? Did you start to see that the world was more unfair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I see it as being more - interesting, because I did work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did starting work change your relationship with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No it didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Nor with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you spend Sunday in a different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. I couldn't you know. I couldn't even sew a button on, and I won't sew a button even today. Not on Sund
ay. I won't you know. Even if their trousers were falling down I wouldn't do it you know. 'Cos I remember the little boy here asking his mother, oh could you put some elastic in my underpants please? And she said, oh go and ask your grandmother, that's me
,
 and the little boy turned round and said, there's no point in my taking it to my grandmother because I mean she won't do anything with a needle and thread on a Sunday, you know - you should know that mum. And I won't either. But I wouldn't say I was a Ch
ristian either. But I've been brought up to that you know, about not working. I must do anything on Sunday. I've got to respect the Sabbath.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I didn't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you spend your free time in a different way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you start going out in the evening?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you make new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Only the friends that were sort of around me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take these friends home with you, to your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Oh maybe I took one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have a special friend at this time, a girl or a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did. One. She was the same ase as me, there was just two hours between us and we'd been to school together and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What sort of things did you do with this friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well, we might go for an outing or to the eistedford in Dolgellau and one of us might say, are you coming? And the other'd say, well - I'll come with you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents always expect to know where you were after you left home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, you see, they knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If you went home did they expect you to be in by a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if I went home, while I was - a servant for the Minister they'd come with me every step back to Talsarnau in the even
ing. They wouldn't let me go by myself. My mother and my sister would come with me all the way. I was too frightened to go by myself. I'd be frightened now too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How old were you when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well if I'd waited a month I'd have been twenty-two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And that was in 1914?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. And my husband was twenty-one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long had you known your husband before you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I met him when I was working for the Minister, when I was about fifteen. But of course you know he wasn
't at home, he was working in South Wales in the coalmine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you meet him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he was a boy from Talsarnau so I got to know him like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you save any money to get married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I had very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your parents help you to set up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. They didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long were you engaged for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Three years I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you tell me about the wedding, what sort of thing was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well there were ten people in the wedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you get presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. Yes. An enormous number of presents - between us that is of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go away on a honeymoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. We only went to Crykyeth for the day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did you live after you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - at Foriw, Talsarnau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And you were by yourselves were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh there must have been six houses, in a terrace, but we had our own house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many years did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we hadn't been there long and then he went to the South, then I went to the South
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh well, I came back to Balaenau after I'd had my first son. He - he came in South Wales. The day he was six weeks old I came back. In fact we came back to Talsarnau first and from there I came up to Oakley Square, then up to Conrog and 
from Conrog down to here. Goodness knows what the next journey'll be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Your husband was twenty-one when you married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What was his job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - wait a minute - he was with a farmers - when he was thirteen - no, when he was thirteen
 he was - in the coalmine in South - Wales, you could go there from school. And he came from the mine and he was with the farmers and he'd spend six months with one and six months somewhere else. And then he went to the South after we got married, to the 
pit again. And then he was so homesick that he nearly died so I had to go down and join him. I took my bed and everything with me, and I've never been any further than Barmouth on the train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you frightened of going?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, terribly. Oh I was so frightened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And then what did you do after he left South Wales for the second time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well when - the boys was six weeks old, he came with me to - to bring me home and he stayed home. And - he stayed - he'd been home about a week and then he 
went into the hay field of the next - of the neighbouring farm and the recruiting officer came from Blaenau and he joined up. And he and the other boy that worked on the farm went and joined the Army. They joined from the hayfield and I was worse than a w
i
dow then. Yes, he went to the Army, he was a Sergeant in the Army you know. He was over in France. He was over in France in December, he went to the Army in August, and he was made a corporal before Christmas and then he went to a school, I've got a pictu
re of him when he was at school and then he was a Sergeant.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did he leave the Army, at the end of the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 19 - 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And then what job did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he was in the quarry after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What was he in the quarry, a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, a rock}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he do any part time jobs while he was working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did your husband feel towards work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he liked it well enough. And he had sort of odds and ends to do when he came home, specially when we were living in 
Conglog, because we had cows there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You said he liked working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many children did you have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When were the ones that were born before 1918 born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the eldest was born on the eighth of May 1915. A
nd the next one was born within three years and three months of that one. That's the second one, and the next one was born within a year and nine months and the next was born within two years of him. And that's Betty, and Betty's fifty. And then Dai comes
 
after that, and Dai's forty-eight in June, that's two years isn't it between them, and I lost one between Dai and Blevin, and Blevin's forty-six. And Arthur's forty-five, a year and four months between them and Peggy's forty-two. That's a step again.; And
 Molly's thirty-eight. And that's them all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were the children born in hospital or at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh at home, they were all born at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you know what to expect in childbirth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I just hoped that they'd be all right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did it go O.K. without any trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any medical help at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I had a doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, everything he could do. And the - the nurse would go as soon as he came back from work and had had his 
tea, and she'd go then and - and he'd help. He was very good like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How soon did you get up after you'd had the baby?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't think I got up any earlier than nine days after. I don't think so. Not like they are now, they come back now yo
u know after about two days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 After nine days did you get up for a whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did. But even then you had to take it easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did the family manage while you were confined to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh all right you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did any relatives or neighbours come round to help you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I had a nurse you see. For two weeks. I paid her for two weeks you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feed the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh some of them were breast fed and others had bottles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you like breast feeding the baby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did. I much prefer breast feeding, oh yes. It's much more natural - and the milk's always warm too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you didn't breast feed how did you manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh with a bottle of milk. I used National Dried or Cow and Goat milk, but Blevin got Nestles. He was O.K. on it too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any difficulties about feeding the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Only with one. He was only four pounds - no, he was eight - only eight pounds when he was four - months old, that was Arthur.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take advice from a doctor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I had to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If the baby }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 as sleeping did you wake it up to feed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I certainly didn't. They'd have to scream their heads off before they got food. I didn't believe in waking them I assure you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If it cried before its feeding time did you give it food?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I put a dummy in its mouth until I'd had time to make its food of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if the baby didn't want its food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I'd try and give it something in case it had something wrong with its sto
mach, but there was one, I think it was crying as it was born, and it used to cry all night too, that's the one who lives in Birmingham.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long did you go on feeding the babies yourself, breast feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the eldest one was a year and 
two months and the doctor in Harlech said to me, what do you feed this boy on? And I said, the breast doctor. He said, it's time you stopped you know, the boys stronger than you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did you give them solid food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well, you know, when they c
ome a bit you give them a little bit of something that you're eating. And if that was O.K. with them then you give them a little bit more, a piece of potato that had been mashed up, when they were somewhere between ten months and year. And you'd sort of m
ake it all sloppy for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the baby take to the food all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel it did the baby any harm if you left it to cry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, it was right for them to cry sometimes, as long as they didn't cry too much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you punish the baby when it was naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean when it was a naughty boy? Yes, well he'd get - the odd shake, or clout. Especially in the night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean for crying in the night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How much interest did your husband take in the babies when they were under a year, did he do things for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. Oh he loved them when they were small, and Blevin likes children too you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband feed them, bath them or change their nappies?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well no, he would - but if I was all right then I did it. I didn't want him to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he play with the babies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes. Yes. But remember this, he had fantastic discipline over them, authority. Not like some are now, they haven't got any control over their children at all. No they haven't you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband get up at night if the child was crying?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, he would. If they were on the bottle he'd get up and feed them, and make the bottle. Fair play to him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he take the children out on his own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, he wouldn't. He was frightened of them beginning to cry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you know how much your husband earned when he was in the quarry or in the coal mine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he didn't get much in the coal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 pit in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I cant remember how much he go either. We used to pay ten shillings for our rooms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 In the South you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. For just a bedroom and a kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he give you the housekeeping money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes he did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How much did you get?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - I don't remember you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you talk to your husband about how to spend the money, how to budget it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we used to struggle you know and owner how it was going to stretch. You had to do it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many rooms did you have in the flat in the South?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh just two. Just a bedroom and kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 O}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 akley Square?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had three bedrooms in Oakley Square and a - a parlour and a kitchen and a little kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And what about Conglog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had three - but we c
ould two beds in one room. We had three bedrooms in Conglog and we used to sleep in the parlour, we'd made that into a bedroom. And then a kitchen. And then we had the next door house, in a way we had two houses 'cos next door was empty and that's where w
e used to eat and wash.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any relatives or lodgers living with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you pay anyone to help you in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you do all the washing at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well I used to send the sheets t
o the laundry, because I mean I had enough work to do with such a big family. It was a very happy time though you know. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about clothes, did you make and mend the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - we'd get a lot of clothes, we'd get material a
nd give them to this woman and she'd make - clothes for the children. Jane was fifteen before she got her first coat from the shop, new coat from the shop. This woman would make coats and trousers and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 hand clothes at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, I didn't like these.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we always had new shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there a special time when you bought new clothes or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh when they'd gone through them.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you usually buy them from Blaenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband help with jobs around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh if I wanted him to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Cleaning and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Iys. And this one's very good at cooking too. (She was living - she lives with one or her sons at the moment, she's 
referring to him) Oh yes, he's very good at cooking. But he leaves - leaves an enormous amount of mess behind him. But that's a man isn't it. Though I don't know, I think men should do things in the house. I think it's better that they should. Otherwise t
hey don't appreciate what hard work it is do they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did repairs and improvements to the house and decorating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - Molly does that 'cos I can't get on chairs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I did it myself then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And your husband did too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband help the children to dress and have their baths?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't remember him doing that. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he read to them or tell them stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No he just gave them warnings that they weren't to make mischief.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And he didn't take them out without you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he look after them when you went out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If I did yes he did. But I didn't go - I hardly went out at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children have any tasks to do for you around the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they had to do. They used to do the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 m}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 uck}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 spreading and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 This was for your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. They had to do it, when we were up in the top in Conglog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they help you in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, very little. The girls would though, but the boys wouldn't. But they went to work you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you send them to bed at a certain time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh when we lived up at the top it was six o'clock and they were in bed, they couldn't stay up later. That was the only five
 minutes peace we'd get so they had to go to bed. And they had to have had a wash before they went. They had to be in bed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did they start going to bed on their own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't know. There was a big crowd of them so they went with each other, they all went together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children share bedrooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - the boys were in the back bedroom and I had one girl with something wrong with her back so she had to have a bed of her own, but the two others went to work, this was in Conglog, 
but when they were younger of course they had to share beds. But I always had three bedrooms and us in the parlour, 'cos we'd made the parlour into a bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about having baths, did they have a tub in a front of the fire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes they did. I had a big boiler in the empty house next door up in Conglog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did they have baths? And when did they have them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they'd have them in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Every night?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no. No. Otherwise they wouldn't have any skin left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did they have clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Every week. But if they got dirty I had to give them new ones - other ones of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did you eat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever eat in any other rooms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. Only in the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you cook in the kitchen too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. But in the kitchen of the other house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean when you were in Conglog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. But we went to live in Plas after that. The - the owner or manager of - the quarry and all the houses around Conglog lived in 
a big house, which is where they went to stay for two years before they came down - back into Blaenau. This family was the last family to leave the - the village, up in the mountains, which is right next to the quarry. And not many people lived up there p
e
rmanently. Quite often workers would stay up there on weekdays and then go home at the weekends, but this family stayed there all the time. Yes, we used to live in Sir Evan Jones's house, the Plas. You know it's just by where we were at first, up at the t
o
p you know. And it was a lovely big house. There's a big kitchen there, much bigger than here, and a place for churning, but I think they churned in the cellar. And there were two big front rooms, lovely they were, and the passage, and it was wide like th
is, it was lovely. And then there was a front door and a porch on the front door and lovely wide stairs going up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many bedrooms were there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 One, two, three - five bedrooms. Oh and they were lovely too. And a cellar to keep coal and wood.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How long did you live there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh we weren't long there. I'm sure we weren't there more than two years. Out of the eighteen when we were up there, because the working rhosydd stopped. That's the highest quarry in Blaenau, the furthest away too from th
e town. And so everyone had to come down after that and now it's gone you know. There isn't even a door on the house. Oh it's terrible you know, 'cos it used to have such lovely doors. Oh it's a shame. It's a great shame, it's a pity. You know I'd like to
 liver there now, but I wouldn't like to live up there without him, you know what I mean, it's too lonely up there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you cook on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we had a large oil}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 stove with fur burners. Well I could put things in the oven too, in the big stove but it wasn't as good as the oil stove, and I used to churn and everything myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did you have breakfast, dinner, tea and supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh breakfast, we used to have breakfast before they went to work in the morning and then the children afterwards
, and the children would go down to school. They had to leave at eight o'clock. And then I'd have dinner all by myself at dinnertime. And then they'd come home at four o'clock from the quarry and they'd have a meal there and then they wouldn't really want
 much after that, after they'd had a big dinner when they came home at four.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have a special dinner on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did you usually have to eat for your meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - for Sunday we used to have potatoes and carrots and cabbage and beef, or any vegetable we could get hold of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about other days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh well - we'd have - porridge and things for breakfast and sometimes eggs and bacon, 'cos we had some animals, and - oh for dinner - when they came in from work there'd
 be stew or something like that. And then they'd have - take sandwiches to work with them to the quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you bake your own bread at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did, but not very much, it was cheaper to buy it in fact - rather than carrying coal right up to t
he top for the oven, there wasn't any sense in that, because I mean half a ton wouldn't - wouldn't last at all up there once you started baking and things in the house and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about making jam, did you do that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I used to make jams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, pickles.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you make wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't know what would have happened if I'd made beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about making medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you bottle fruit and vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No I didn't try and do any of that, only pickles and chutney. Oh I had pickles - ooh - everything, lot - worth lots of money. I gave an enormous big jar like this to the three girls who were in Betta's and I - I give stuff to Molly too because 
she lives near here. And Molly often makes the chutney, so I used to - I give her the ingredients for it and she makes it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you buy vegetables at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I did, 'cos we couldn't really grow very much in Conglog, it was too high.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you buy tinned things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What animals did you have up in Conglog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
We had two cows, we could have kept three actually, and we had a calf, but we couldn't keep the calf for long, we had to get - do away with it or send it away. We kept pigs there and hens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband look after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, and me. Me mostly. 'Cos I was there all through the day by myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times in a week would you have meat to eat?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well wed have meat on Sunday and maybe some
body'd go down and we'd have some steak or some chops or something and we'd have bacon or ham and I'd try and make a - a bit of dinner. I'd try and give them meat once a day anyway. But I didn't always manage it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about tinned meat, did you have corned Beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes, we did. Oh but that's gone expensive now hasn't it. It's six shillings a tin you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about getting extra meat through poaching, did you ever do any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we'd get that in Tanygrisiau - when we were in Con
glog that was. Monny would go down on - on the back of the pony, ride the pony down and - and get - meat from a man in - from my man in Tanyrrisiau. She'd go down and get a leg or something you know every Saturday, for Sunday this would be, or may be one 
or two chops. And then when they were coming home from school they might bring something up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was this from the butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Yes that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about poaching?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Poaching? Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. I don't think so. I don't think anyone felt inclined to poach, anyone of them. They fished though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you ever remember having less food in order that your husband and children should have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I got what I wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband have more food than the rest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you emphasise the children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 s manners at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No I didn't. They were supposed to ask if they could leave the table and this is what I say to these lot now, my grandchildren, they were supposed to ask - and that's wh
at I said to mine, but you know they've gone over the crockery now, they're old enough to know to - to - you know - to be their own - to make their own decisions.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were the children allowed to talk during mealtimes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the odd one would, the odd one though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were your children allowed to choose what they wanted to eat or did they have to eat everything that was five to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they couldn't choose, oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have to eat everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they take the salt from the table or did they have to wait until it was offered to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - they took it. Otherwise it'd never come to an end would it with all of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could they ask for a second helping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, if they wanted to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you make them hold their knives and forks in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about sitting in a special way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. But they used to quarrel - but they knew where they were supposed to sit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about bringing toys and books to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No they couldn't do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did all the family sit down at the table if they were all there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they all sit in the same places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you serve the food out to them?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you give the food out in any particular order, did you give it to your husband first and then the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well what I'd do would be to put a big bowl of potatoes on the table and then maybe I'd have given the meat out to them, it would be on their plates alrea
dy and then there'd be a bowl of carrots or cabbage, you know, which had been cut up, then - they could - they could help themselves to that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband take the food first and then the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes that's right, he took it first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened to the children when they were small, where did they eat then, before they could feed themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh well, you know, once they'd come to about two or three they joined us at the table, and as far as I remember before that they used to sit on my knee or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you had small children did you think that there was a correct and incorrect way of bringing them up, do you remember thinking that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I don't know. I mean I did everything I could - I did what was right in my 
mind, and if they were ill or something, I mean all I could do was try and - and - be a doctor to them or get the doctor to come to them if they were bad. 'Cos if I couldn't do anything myself there was nothing else to do but send for the doctor.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that there was a correct way of bringing up children, a right way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I can tell you this. Well Mrs Williams, Gwyn Weilliams' mother, you know, he's a curate in Caernarvon, well she said that they never had to raise a finger to the childr
en from Conglog. That they respected everybody when they - when they came down to school and when they went back again. She said, it's a great credit to you, they've been taught to behave. She never had to shout at them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say your husband and you had the same ideas about bringing up children, did you see eye to eye about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you talk about bringing up children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no. They came so often. We never talked about whether we were going to have one or not.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have discussions about how to bring them up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, as far as I know. I don't know. I don't remember quite honestly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was there anyone you could talk to when you were worried about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well I would worry and I worry today too if there's something wrong with them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did you talk to about the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh Mrs Williams, Gwyn Willia}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 ms' mother, he's a curate in Ca}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 rnarvon you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was your mother alive when the children were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well wait a minute, she died - well Peggy never saw her. And Peggy's forty-two in September. Nor my father either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often did the other children see their grandfather and grandmother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well Dai - Dai was with them an awful lot, but Owen really didn't see very much 
of them. The thing was that they had a farm you see and the children liked to go over there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever ask your mother for advice about how to bring up the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I didn't see very much of her you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't see much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. You see she lived up above Harlech and we were up in Blaenau so I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about your husband's mother, your mother-in-law, did you ask her advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she lived in Talsarnau.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you see very much of her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I would see her, we used to go for a walk to Talsarnau sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ask her for advice?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say your mother-in-law and your mother dad the same ideas about rearing children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't know, but I think their Talsarnau
 grandmother had - eleven children. She's Arthur Williams and Avie Williams' mother you know. He was the eldest son. My husband that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you tell me what things you felt you ought to do for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I felt that they ought to resp
ect people and they shouldn't do anything out of place, they shouldn't touch anything that didn't belong to them and they'd always be told that, and they shouldn't - shoot their mouths off about anything and they should give older people a seat if they we
re in a bus and that they should stand. And they had to respect everybody. And not be rude to anyone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you want them to share their worries with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. They - they did though.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel you ought to show affection to them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And keeping them safe and feeding them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, naturally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you were talking did you allow your children to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, they were glad to go out and play a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if somebody hit your children, another child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I didn't have very much temper in those days, I've got much more now you know. If I see someone doing something to them now my temper's much worse now than it was. I don't know if it's something to do with the illness so I had, I've certai
nly got more temper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you want them to hit the children back if you saw them being mistreated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well that's what everybody does now, and they say if somebody does something to you then you do it back. But I don't - I don't agree with that. I r
eally don't. I say, leave them alone and just carry on because it only leads to something more if you start hitting people back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were there any children that you felt you didn't want your children to play with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. But anyway most of the time th
ey were up the top and - they couldn't play with anyone up there. Only by themselves. But when they were on Oakley Square they used to play, but I used to w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 rn them, I used to say, be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 careful that you don't do mischievous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
 things. Go round being naughty. I don't want to hear of you doing it anywhere. But one of them, I think he }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9580749\charrsid13268011 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
roke a window down in Taygrisiau and the lady came up and told me off and I said, well, wait 'til he gets home and he'll hear about it. And - bus she said to me, I don't put all the 
blame on you you know. I know you've brought them up well. And I said, yes, I mean I've taught them not to trespass on anybody's place or do anything - or destr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551638\charrsid13268011 o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 y anything. And she said, oh I know, Mrs Williams. And the poor creature's in her grave for a long - since a long time now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If the children did things that you disapproved of what happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I'd clout them if I could get near them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you do this often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well if they did things against me often I did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband hit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I can't remember him hitting them. No, no - no recollection of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember a particular occasion on which you punished them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, well - I had this some you see that used to have a rubber heel on it and it - and I u
sed it against Dai, the one that's with the - you know - selling insurance now, and he was shouting and refusing to do something and I picked up this shoe and hit him on the top of his head, this was in Conglog, and the blood was spouting up out of his he
ad. I didn't think you know, 'cos the - the rubber heel had gone. And there was a screw in it. I remember that today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was he O.K., it didn't affect him badly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, he's all right. Talks all right anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say the children received
 the ideas they have about how to behave from you or your husband or from both of you, who would you say affected them most?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I think he did really. He had most control over them. But I don't think any of them didn't - you know - refused to listen 
to either of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't work after you had children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes I did. I used to go to Cefnbychan, after I'd sent the children off to school in the morning. I'd go there to wash, and I'd get half a crown for doing it. And I'd bring eighteen
 shirts home to wash, 'cos I had a boiler, and six starched collars. Half a crown. We'd do it today? And I used to cut firewood too, saw up sleepers. Well they'd be cut up into logs and then I'd - chop them up smaller and bundle them up. I had to do that 
you know otherwise I just couldn't make ends - ends meet.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You only did this work when your children were at school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you make anything of your children}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551638\charrsid13268011 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 s birthdays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - it's only recently that they've 
had a card and something small. But Blevin doesn't believe in birthday cards or Christmas cards or anything. No. No he doesn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Does he think it's wasting money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I suppose so, but he wastes enough in other ways you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you give them something special to eat on their birthday? Like pancakes or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - no, no. Although today you know I mean it's a great big thing, a birthday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh they'd get a little on Christmas Day. A kitbag or - and some
 oranges or sweets or something like that. On maybe they'd have a wooden doll. But very little I assure you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have anything special to eat on Christmas Day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, Christmas dinner, we'd have a goose or a turkey or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any musical instruments in your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 There was a small harmonium, that's all. But Monny didn't do very much with it, and I had two pianos.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you play it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, to suit myself I did, yes. Now wait a minute, we had a harmonia and an organ and then a piano. But I've sold them now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did anyone play them seriously?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about singing, did anyone of you sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well Blevin sang - sings. But I say he's just making a noise.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they compete in the eistedford, either singing or reciting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't think they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever have a musical evening in your home, with the piano and singing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I - I only used to play my things you know, things I made up. I used to enjoy myse
lf on the piano. I took it from this woman, she didn't want it. But then there wasn't room here either so I got rid of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you play games with your children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband join in too? Did you play games as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well he'd play draughts and things, and ludo, but he didn't like dominoes and he didn't like cards. But I mean he would play them but he didn't like it, if it was wet or something he'd have to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any books in your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes I g
ot - there's an enormous amount in the shed back there. You see, I don't read but he did. And they're very old books too, the ones in the shed. I'm sure they're worth something, I don't know. I just want to get rid of them this summer. They're down in the
 bottom of the garden, in the shed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 So your husband read a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh yes, he did. He'd get books from the library to read and everything. But I wasn't ever one for reading, I never read a comic you know. Nor these books. I never read any.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about newspapers, did you get them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I'd look at the Welsh newspaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you get a newspaper?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - I don't get one now, I get it from Mrs Roberts or Mrs Williams.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have newspapers when your husband was alive?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, we had a paper then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any magazines at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Where did you get your books or newspapers from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we got them from will Maydyon, he's over the road from the Commercial and he married Miss Jones the chemist, 
and she lived in the chemist shop next door to the library.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you belong to the library?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes we did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't read loud to the children did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. I was never any good at reading stories.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take the children out to visit friends, relatives or neighbours at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't take them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take the children shopping?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. It was enough for me to shop by myself, I didn't want them along with me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You've already said they didn't go out with your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did anything special happen on a Bank Holiday? Did you go somewhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh no, we - we hardly went at all. I've never been on a holiday anywhere you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you spend Saturdays - you and the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, I'd be preparing for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the children go to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, yes, they went all the way from Congrog every Sunday, they came down to here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times did they go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, they only really went in the morning, because I had cows you see and we had to deal with those first. They had to be kil}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551638\charrsid13268011 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
ed and everything. Just really one or two of them would go down in the morning, but they went every Sunday afternoon to Sunday school to this little chap
el here, and the one next to the eldest would stay in number thirteen here with the - with the son of number thirteen and he'd be sure to go to - to chapel in the evening, and the eldest one too. But I haven't much recollection of Dai, but Blevin used to 
go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did they have to wear special clothes for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, their best clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel it was wrong to play or work on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You mean for us to do it? Well I don't like anyone to work on a Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you allow your children to play games on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. But they're over the crockery now, so I can't say anything to them anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go down to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't. I used to go to the small chapel, to Sunday school, but I didn't go there af
ter I broke my arm, I broke my arm in the street and I broke the other one under the table and it's still crooked, and I didn't go after I'd broken my arm, down to the little chapel. But it's gone now I mean, they haven't been using it for years now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 So you weren't going to church any more, you went to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, I went to the Wesleyan chapel after I got married you see. Although I was brought up church of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did your husband go to the chapel?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, the Wesleyan chapel he did. But he didn't go down from Conglog either, but when we were in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14551638\charrsid13268011 Oa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
kley Square he used to go. Either him or me every Sunday morning, we used to go to rhiw and if I went in the morning he'd be at home making the dinner and then the other one would go in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you belong to the choir?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you remember there being a temperance club attached to the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you belong to anything else connected with the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you say grace before meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about family prayers, did you have those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you teach your children to say prayers before they went to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I taught them but I've no idea how many of them do. I sometimes ask this one and I have seen him on his knee
s many times so he gets pardoned no doubt. Oh you know he was terrible when he came from the sea, this is Bleddyn. He couldn't come up to Conglog by himself at all. You see, the boat was split in half, was broken in half, and he could only get out by walk
ing across lots of bodies, it's the only way he could get out of the boat to another boat and h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14551638\charrsid13268011 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
s nerves were really terrible after that and then he's had so many accidents in the quarry since then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you take an interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about your husband, did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't know. He was a great labour man. But I don't think he was stupid that way either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you know why he voted Labour?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I don't know. I used to sign of the Labour people too, but I don't know why. I sup
pose it was just 'cos my husband did, I don't really know anything about it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember your husband voting before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I don't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you ever remember you or your husband being under any pressure to vote for a particular pa
rty, that someone was trying to make up your minds for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were you or your husband a member of a political party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well you see they'd come round to collect, the Labour party would in the old days, collect money, and he'd contribut
e every time. He was a Labour man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he work at election times for the Labour party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, he did, as far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he take part in any political activities apart from at election time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you weren't working what did you and your husband do in your spare time, did you have any hobbies or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh we'd do some mending or something. There weren't many five minutes to be had with such a household. Houseful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 You didn't go out in the evening or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, no, we didn't. We'd come out on - on Friday night to shop, that's all. We'd come down from Conglog for that, or else if we'd gone short of something. Or}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011  I'd come down and get a whole }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 pannier full and take it all the way up to Cwmrog.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When did your husband finish work in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well it would be getting on for five by the time he was home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often was he in during the evening, did he go out at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, he used to go out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How many times would he go out in a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh I can't remember. But not much. He did go a bit more once we came down to live here, but then he got taken ill and he was ill for seven years here. He got rheumatoid arthritis and he couldn't do anything, and he's been dead now for fifteen years.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he go to pubs or clubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No he didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he belong to any clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever go out together to a pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I went once and I've regretted it ever since you know. I really have.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well I was supposed to be going to Barmouth you see, and I used to go on a Friday evening until Sunday, just to - just go and visit my sister you see, and he said to me he was just going to call in to the
 new - to the North Western and - he just put his head in through the door, that's what he said, I don't know what it's like there now though. Right, I said. He said he'd be out when the bus came, and my eldest daughter was with me. And I looked at - alon
g
 the road a bit and I saw this man and this man said that - said to my husband that I was out there you see and this man came up to me, what will you have, he said. Good Lord, I'll have nothing, I said. I - I'm not used to it, I've never had it. Oh, he sa
i
d, and he went back inside and he came out with a small glass of port. Good Lord, I haven't got used to drinking, I said. Come here, he said, no one'll see you here. And he opened the door of the smoke room I think it is isn't it, I can't remember, anyway
 
it's opposite the - the bottom door. Oh don't talk to me, I went into a den of thieves there. Everyone - I knew everyone there, they all knew me and I took a tiny swig of this drink and I put it under the chair and - and I said to Jane, my daughter, come 
o
n, let's get out of here. And - and we left, and that's the first time and the last time that I ever went into a pub and that's true. And Bleddyn sometimes says to me, oh come down for a bellyful of beer. And I just say, yes, you go yourself if you want i
t.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you belong to a savings club at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I have savings now but I didn't then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any money saved up towards sickness or funerals or boots and shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, no. We had to pay the doctor, but then that got - came - ree.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you or your husband take part in sports at all? Football or cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 He did go fishing, yes, yes. But he didn't do any to the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Sh}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011 oo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 ting?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did he go cycling or walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I used to go on a bike, you know, long ago, and I did go once from here you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever bet on anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Bet? Betting? Yes, I put the odd shilling on a horse sometimes. Well I'd do it if he did you see, I did - I wouldn't like to do it by myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about going to the theatre or concerts or music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the pictures?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, I used to go to the pictures a little bit, that was when I was down in Oakley Square, but not after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any hobbies, did you keep any pets or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No - well I had - you know, ducks and hens and geese - and a pig.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you do the a garden as a hobby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well we didn't have a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any interests outside the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well, I only used to try and - and keep it tidy you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have interests outside the house, did you go out, did you have any interests which took you outside - away from the house?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No I didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever go out to enjoy yourself in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did anyone come from outside to help you with the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - if there was something heavy that had to me moved, yes, maybe yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Friends and neighbours would come in would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, that's right. You see, when I was in Oakley Aquare I use - to try and help everybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What happened if you had to stay in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well they had to try and suffer themselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No we didn't. Only the children. There was nobody but us up in the top you know. No. It was only us up in Conglon you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Wasn't there anyone else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well - Mrs Pugh was there for a bit and Baker Wilson was there, but only for a very short time. There was nobody in the whole valley apart from us. And you could shout and scream as much as you liked and no one could hear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any friends, did any friends come up to see you in Conglog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh only about two. Mrs Hughes from Oakley Square.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you share the same friends as your husband?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes, of course.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you have any friends of your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, but I mean I was friends with everybody. I don't think I've got any enemies. I don't think so anyway.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 If your friends came to the house would they be given something to eat or drink?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well yes, Mrs Williams does, she's the only one that comes here you know, except for people who come with the laundry or the cleaners or something. But apart from that I don't think anyone else comes now. Not, you know, to stay - to eat something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did any friends or neighbours that did call come without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh yes. If they came you know. In fact I didn't invite anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you go and see your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you remember making your own amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I quite comfortable myself, by myself. I do what I can myself. But it means nagging this old boy here a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Was your house rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What this one, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 The one at the top?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh all I had to do there was repairs and keep it in order, there wasn't any rent.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you see anything of the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, it was Sir Evan you know, and you see what happened was if something went wrong and the roof needed mending or something well we had to do it, and we had to pay for it. Otherwise we just p
aid a shilling a year, sort of formal rent. And we had to do all the repairs ourselves.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I felt all right towards him, when we saw him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who would you say were the important people in Blaenau, what sort of people were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 In Blaenau? Oh there's a lot of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What type of people, do you remember any special ones, don't you remember any people who you thought were big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 nobs, anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh you}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 re asking me a question now.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Who did the shopkeepers mix with? Who were their friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well - the ones that paid them best, that's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the Ministers and teachers, who did they mix with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you come across them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, I don't see many minis
ters around at all. There aren't any you know now. They don't go round visiting you now you know. That's finished for many a day now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the farmers, who did they mix with? Did they stick with other farmers or did they mix in with the community as a whole?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh I don't know - there aren't many that do that, that mix in with the community. But then again they don't mix with each other because - they seem to be jealous of each other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the employers, did you see much of them, the quarry owners or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No. No we didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did the - keep together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes, yes that's right they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say there's any difference between church people and chapel people in }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011 B}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 laenau?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well I think the church people are very mean and very narrow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Why do you think that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well they want everything for themselves they do. There isn't any relief anywhere you know. I mean there's no }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11560224\charrsid13268011 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 hristianity, you can be sure of that. No there isn't. There's always this jealousy between one person and another or the church and the chapel.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say that all the workers in Blaenau had the same standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well they've a much better standard now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would you say there's a big difference amongst workers though?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Yes there is. Well the thing is actually that it's the owners who get everything and the - and the - the sort of dregs, the workers don't get anything. Still that is. Is that what you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Were there any differences between the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't know. But if I worked in the - you know, in the midst of them I'd probably know you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Do you think that some workers felt that they were superior to others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I don't know. I suppose the odd one did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about the difference between craftsmen and labourers in Blaenau, was there any distinction made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Would the people respect the craftsman more in Blaenau than they do the ordinary labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh I'm sure they do. Oh yes, I'm quite sure they do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 When you were bringing up the children did you have trouble making ends meet? Did you have trouble getting enough money and enough to eat?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes it want - it was impossible to get enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did you feel towards this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 I felt I'd like to have a lot more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you feel angry towards anyone or anything because of this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
No, I just had to accept what I'd got you know and do what I could with it. I mean there wasn't anything else to do was there, but it was hard you know, it was very hard then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did it make any difference to you if your husband was ill or out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Yes. Yes it did, certainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 There wasn't any insurance or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, there was very little insurance in those days was there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How often was he out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Oh I don't know that he was ever out of work except for the time when something happened to his hands, just the last six years that's all. You see - but before that he'd had dermatitis on his hands you know from the 
oil, and he was off work for three months then. I mean there was a little insurance then you know but it was very small. The only thing that was advantageous to us was that we had - milk and butter ourselves you know which was something to fall back on, o
therwise it would have been very very difficult to - to survive.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Did you ever have charity from the parish at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 No, no, not at all. Not - not until - my husband died and then I got Social Security - assistance. I've never asked - I never asked
 for it and I didn't ask either. I never asked for anything ; not like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 How did they treat you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 
Well you know they treat people - people who are young enough to have jobs, they treat them well, they get everything you know in this country. 
They get everything, they have motorbikes, car or a cupboard for the house and they - they destroy. They don't even try and wash or anything. But - but sometimes - they - they - both of them will be working too as well as getting assistance, but there's a
 new scheme coming isn't there and they'll be caught, they'll be caught.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Could you just tell me what jobs your children have done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Well the eldest one works at Etchells at the tool}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7302947\charrsid13268011 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 making factory in - in Blaenau Ffestioniog. That's Owen M}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7302947\charrsid13268011 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 redith.
 And Roberts in Birmingham, I' don't know what he's doing. He's fifty-two or fifty-three.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did he do first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well he went with the farmers first.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What did the one working in Etchells do first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh he went to the - to the quarry f
irst. But he had a very bad accident and he was home for a very long time, and he's in Etchells now, but I don't know what he one in Birmingham's doing. He was in a factory, I know that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 And the oldest girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh she keeps a cafe in Betws Y Coed. 
And the other girl is looking after a school, is a caretaker of a school and the other one works in the Post Office shop. But of course I mean she has to do her housework as well, she's got two girls. And then Arthur works in a quarry and he does light - 
light work there now and Bleddyn - he does a light job in the quarry now. And Dai's with insurance and Monnies here, next door. And she's working in Etchells now. She's just started there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 What about their first jobs though, what did they do to begin with, what did Belddyn do first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5899499 JW  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 Oh well he went to the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4202737 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9991975\charrsid13268011 After the Navy did he go to the quarry?
